[{"id":"VR803593","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a rectangular conductor connected to a circuit. The circuit is rectangular and has a battery on its lower horizontal branch and has an open switch on its left vertical branch. The conductor is on the upper horizontal branch. Point A is indicated at the top of the conductor. Point B is indicated at the bottom of the conductor. The conductor is centered in a rectangular region labeled B-Field Into Page.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR803593.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A rectangular metallic conductor is connected by copper wires in series with a battery and a switch as shown. The conductor lies within a region containing a uniform magnetic field directed into the page. A voltmeter is connected across points <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math></span></span> such that if Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math></span></span> is at a higher potential, the voltmeter will read a positive value. With the switch open, the voltmeter reads <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"0 volts\"><math alttext=\"0 volts\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>0</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi></math></span></span>. A short time after the switch is closed what is the sign of the value the voltmeter reads?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR803593_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">A positive value</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Zero</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">A negative value</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">A value alternating between positive and negative</p>"],"answer":2}]